Australia has a long history of film production. Australia's first dedicated film studio, the [[Limelight Department]], was created by The [[Salvation Army]] in Melbourne in 1898, and is believed to have been the world's first.<ref>http://www.salvationarmy.org.au/SALV/STANDARD/PC_60860.html</ref> The world's first feature-length film was the Australian production ''[[The Story of the Kelly Gang]]'' of 1906.<ref>http://aso.gov.au/titles/features/story-kelly-gang</ref> After such early successes, Australian cinema suffered from the rise of [[Hollywood]].
